race.comment: COMPELLING TRUTH (1) climbed through the grades last campaign - highlighted by his Listed Wagga Town Plate win. That form has repeatedly translated well in South Australia, with the likes of Santa Ana Lane and Front Page both proving that profile stacks up. Two sharp trials have him right where he needs to be. SGHIRRIPA (2) rediscovered something close to his top last start off a 63-day freshen, finding plenty late to keep them all at bay. Full of confidence now, he can keep the roll going. WONDER BOY (7) crosses the border and, while he's probably looking for further, he'll relish the strong tempo and can be charging late off their backs. CINQUE TORRI (6) was solid fresh. This is tougher but he won't know himself under this weight. Keeping safe.
